RE: the "too large" comments:

@720p, 10MB per minute is crap quality. 20 MB/min is decent. Great quality really starts at file sizes around 30 MB/min and over.
Personally, I have a relatively small (woefully small, really) HD, and a pretty slow DL speed once I go over the monthly quota...But I don't want to spoil my own experience by DLing GOT - with its landscape shots, costumes, etc - in small size and poor quality. 

I USED to. But those times are long past...Good image+sound make everything a completely different beast...
